46HloOpcode UnaryOperationToHloOpcode(UnaryOperation unop) {
47 switch (unop) {
48 case UNOP_ABS:
49 return HloOpcode::kAbs;
50 case UNOP_CEIL:
51 return HloOpcode::kCeil;
52 case UNOP_COS:
53 return HloOpcode::kCos;
54 case UNOP_EXP:
55 return HloOpcode::kExp;
56 case UNOP_FLOOR:
57 return HloOpcode::kFloor;
58 case UNOP_IMAG:
59 return HloOpcode::kImag;
60 case UNOP_IS_FINITE:
61 return HloOpcode::kIsFinite;
62 case UNOP_LOG:
63 return HloOpcode::kLog;
64 case UNOP_NOT:
65 return HloOpcode::kNot;
66 case UNOP_NEGATE:
67 return HloOpcode::kNegate;
68 case UNOP_REAL:
69 return HloOpcode::kReal;
70 case UNOP_ROUND_NEAREST_AFZ:
71 return HloOpcode::kRoundNearestAfz;
72 case UNOP_SIGN:
73 return HloOpcode::kSign;
74 case UNOP_SIN:
75 return HloOpcode::kSin;
76 case UNOP_SORT:
77 return HloOpcode::kSort;
78 case UNOP_TANH:
79 return HloOpcode::kTanh;
80 default:
81 LOG(FATAL) << "unhandled operation " << unop;
82 }
83}

156/* static */ StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<UserComputation>>
157UserComputation::MakeWithRemapping(
158 const SessionComputation& session_computation,
159 const ComputationHandle& handle,
160 const std::map<int64, ComputationHandle>& old_to_new) {
161 auto user_computation =
162 MakeUnique<UserComputation>(session_computation.name(), handle);
163 {
164 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(user_computation->mutex_);
165 user_computation->session_computation_ = session_computation;
166 user_computation->next_handle_value_ =
167 std::max_element(session_computation.requests().begin(),
168 session_computation.requests().end(),
169 [](const std::pair<int64, OperationRequest>& lhs,
170 const std::pair<int64, OperationRequest>& rhs) {
171 return lhs.first < rhs.first;
172 })
173 ->first +
174 1;
175 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(user_computation->RemapEmbeddedComputations(old_to_new));
176 }
177
178 return std::move(user_computation);
179}
180
181UserComputation::UserComputation(const string& name,
182 const ComputationHandle& handle)
183 : name_(name), next_handle_value_(1) {
184 *session_computation_.mutable_computation_handle() = handle;
185 session_computation_.set_name(name);
186
187 VLOG(1) << "New UserComputation \"" << name
188 << "\", handle: " << handle.handle();
189}
190
191ComputationDataHandle UserComputation::CreateComputationDataHandle() {
192 ComputationDataHandle handle;
193 handle.set_handle(next_handle_value_);
194 // Handles are used as Version values and *must* be assigned consecutively for
195 // computation versioning to work.
196 next_handle_value_++;
197 return handle;
198}
199
200StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddParameterInstruction(
201 const ParameterRequest& parameter_request) {
202 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
203
204 int64 parameter_number = parameter_request.parameter();
205 if (parameters_.count(parameter_number) != 0) {
206 return InvalidArgument("parameter %lld already registered",
207 parameter_number);
208 }
209 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
210
211 const Shape& validated_shape = parameter_request.shape();
212 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
213 ShapeUtil::ValidateShapeWithOptionalLayout(validated_shape));
214
215 OperationRequest& request =
216 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
217 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
218 *request.mutable_output_shape() = validated_shape;
219 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_parameter_request() = parameter_request;
220
221 parameters_[parameter_number] = &request;
222
223 VLOG(1) << "AddParameterInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
224 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
225 << parameter_request.ShortDebugString();
226 return handle;
227}
228
229StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddSendInstruction(
230 const SendRequest& send_request) {
231 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
232
233 // Check if the operand of the instruction is valid.
234 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(LookUpRequest(send_request.operand()).status());
235
236 // No handle is returned, but a handle must be assigned to this instruction
237 // for computation versioning.
238 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
239 OperationRequest& request =
240 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
241 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
242 *request.mutable_output_shape() = ShapeUtil::MakeNil();
243 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_send_request() = send_request;
244
245 VLOG(1) << "AddSendInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
246 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
247 << send_request.ShortDebugString();
248 return handle;
249}

270StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddPadInstruction(
271 const PadRequest& pad_request) {
272 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
273
274 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* operand,
275 LookUpRequest(pad_request.operand()));
276
277 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* padding_value,
278 LookUpRequest(pad_request.padding_value()));
279

281 operand->output_shape(),
282 padding_value->output_shape(),
283 pad_request.padding_config()));
284
285 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
286 OperationRequest& request =
287 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
288 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
289 *request.mutable_output_shape() = inferred_shape;
290 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_pad_request() = pad_request;
291
292 VLOG(1) << "AddPadInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
293 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
294 << pad_request.ShortDebugString();
295 return handle;
296}

319StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddGatherInstruction(
320 const GatherRequest& gather_request) {
321 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
322
323 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* input_request,
324 LookUpRequest(gather_request.input()));
325 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* gather_indices_request,
326 LookUpRequest(gather_request.gather_indices()));
327
328 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
329 Shape shape,
330 ShapeInference::InferGatherShape(
331 input_request->output_shape(), gather_indices_request->output_shape(),
332 gather_request.dimension_numbers(),
333 AsInt64Slice(gather_request.window_bounds())));
334
335 const ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
336
337 OperationRequest& request =
338 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
339 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
340 *request.mutable_output_shape() = shape;
341 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_gather_request() = gather_request;
342
343 VLOG(1) << "AddGatherInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
344 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
345 << gather_request.ShortDebugString();
346 return handle;
347}

349StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddGetTupleElementInstruction(
350 const GetTupleElementRequest& get_tuple_element_request) {
351 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
352
353 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* operand,
354 LookUpRequest(get_tuple_element_request.operand()));
355 if (!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(operand->output_shape())) {
356 return InvalidArgument(
357 "Operand to GetTupleElement() is not a tuple; got %s",
358 ShapeUtil::HumanString(operand->output_shape()).c_str());
359 }
360 Shape element_shape = ShapeUtil::GetTupleElementShape(
361 operand->output_shape(), get_tuple_element_request.index());
362
363 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
364
365 OperationRequest& request =
366 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
367 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
368 *request.mutable_output_shape() = element_shape;
369 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_get_tuple_element_request() =
370 get_tuple_element_request;
371
372 VLOG(1) << "AddGetTupleElementInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
373 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
374 << get_tuple_element_request.ShortDebugString();
375 return handle;
376}

397StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddRngInstruction(
398 const RngRequest& rng_request) {
399 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
400
401 // Check the number of parameters per RNG distribution.
402 switch (rng_request.distribution()) {
403 case RandomDistribution::RNG_NORMAL:
404 case RandomDistribution::RNG_UNIFORM:
405 if (rng_request.parameter_size() != 2) {
406 return InvalidArgument(
407 "RNG distribution (%s) expects 2 parameters, but got %d",
408 RandomDistribution_Name(rng_request.distribution()).c_str(),
409 rng_request.parameter_size());
410 }
411 break;
412 default:
413 LOG(FATAL) << "unhandled distribution " << rng_request.distribution();
414 }
415
416 // Verify that the parameter indices are valid;
417 for (const ComputationDataHandle& param : rng_request.parameter()) {
418 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(LookUpRequest(param).status());
419 }
420 const Shape& validated_shape = rng_request.shape();
421 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
422 ShapeUtil::ValidateShapeWithOptionalLayout(validated_shape));
423
424 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
425
426 OperationRequest& request =
427 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
428 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
429 *request.mutable_output_shape() = validated_shape;
430 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_rng_request() = rng_request;
431
432 VLOG(1) << "AddRngInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
433 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
434 << rng_request.ShortDebugString();
435 return handle;
436}

438StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddMapInstruction(
439 const MapRequest& map_request,
440 const UserComputation& to_apply_computation) {
441 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
442
443 std::vector<const Shape*> operand_shapes;
444 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle : map_request.operands()) {
445 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* operand, LookUpRequest(handle));
446 operand_shapes.push_back(&operand->output_shape());
447 }
448
449 VersionedComputationHandle::Version to_apply_version =
450 to_apply_computation.version();
451 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
452 std::shared_ptr<const ProgramShape> to_apply_program_shape,
453 to_apply_computation.ComputeProgramShape(to_apply_version));
454 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
455 Shape inferred_shape,
456 ShapeInference::InferMapShape(operand_shapes, *to_apply_program_shape,
457 AsInt64Slice(map_request.dimensions())));
458
459 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
460
461 OperationRequest& request =
462 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
463 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
464 *request.mutable_output_shape() = inferred_shape;
465 request.add_embedded_computation_versions(to_apply_version);
466 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_map_request() = map_request;
467
468 VLOG(1) << "AddMapInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
469 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
470 << map_request.ShortDebugString();
471 return handle;
472}

474StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddReduceInstruction(
475 const ReduceRequest& reduce_request,
476 const UserComputation& to_apply_computation) {
477 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
478
479 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* operand,
480 LookUpRequest(reduce_request.operand()));
481 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* init_value,
482 LookUpRequest(reduce_request.init_value()));
483
484 VersionedComputationHandle::Version to_apply_version =
485 to_apply_computation.version();
486 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
487 std::shared_ptr<const ProgramShape> to_apply_program_shape,
488 to_apply_computation.ComputeProgramShape(to_apply_version));
489
490 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
491 Shape inferred_shape,
492 ShapeInference::InferReduceShape(
493 operand->output_shape(), init_value->output_shape(),
494 AsInt64Slice(reduce_request.dimensions()), *to_apply_program_shape));
495
496 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
497
498 OperationRequest& request =
499 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
500 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
501 *request.mutable_output_shape() = inferred_shape;
502 request.add_embedded_computation_versions(to_apply_version);
503 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_reduce_request() = reduce_request;
504
505 VLOG(1) << "AddReduceInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
506 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
507 << reduce_request.ShortDebugString();
508 return handle;
509}

1244StatusOr<ComputationDataHandle> UserComputation::AddCallInstruction(
1245 const CallRequest& call_request,
1246 const UserComputation& to_apply_computation) {
1247 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
1248
1249 std::vector<const Shape*> operand_shapes;
1250 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle : call_request.operands()) {
1251 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* operand, LookUpRequest(handle));
1252 operand_shapes.push_back(&operand->output_shape());
1253 }
1254
1255 VersionedComputationHandle::Version to_apply_version =
1256 to_apply_computation.version();
1257 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1258 std::shared_ptr<const ProgramShape> to_apply_program_shape,
1259 to_apply_computation.ComputeProgramShape(to_apply_version));
1260 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1261 Shape inferred_shape,
1262 ShapeInference::InferCallShape(operand_shapes, *to_apply_program_shape));
1263
1264 ComputationDataHandle handle = CreateComputationDataHandle();
1265
1266 OperationRequest& request =
1267 (*session_computation_.mutable_requests())[handle.handle()];
1268 *request.mutable_output_handle() = handle;
1269 *request.mutable_output_shape() = inferred_shape;
1270 request.add_embedded_computation_versions(to_apply_version);
1271 *request.mutable_request()->mutable_call_request() = call_request;
1272
1273 VLOG(1) << "AddCallInstruction (" << GetVersionedHandleInternal()
1274 << "), data handle " << handle.handle() << ": "
1275 << call_request.ShortDebugString();
1276 return handle;
1277}

1507Status UserComputation::SetReturnValue(const ComputationDataHandle& handle) {
1508 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
1509
1510 if (!(handle.handle() > 0 && handle.handle() < next_handle_value_)) {
1511 return InvalidArgument("Invalid handle in SetReturnValue");
1512 }
1513
1514 handle_to_return_ = handle;
1515
1516 VLOG(1) << "SetReturnValue of computation \"" << name() << "\" fixed to "
1517 << GetVersionedHandleInternal();
1518
1519 return Status::OK();
1520}

1522VersionedComputationHandle UserComputation::GetVersionedHandle() const {
1523 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
1524 return GetVersionedHandleInternal();
1525}
1526
1527VersionedComputationHandle UserComputation::GetVersionedHandleInternal() const {
1528 VersionedComputationHandle versioned_handle;
1529 versioned_handle.handle = session_computation_.computation_handle();
1530
1531 if (handle_to_return_.handle() > 0) {
1532 // A specific handle has been requested for the result of the computation.
1533 versioned_handle.version = handle_to_return_.handle();
1534 } else {
1535 // A version value is simply the most recently assigned
1536 // ComputationDataHandle value, ie the handle value of the root of the
1537 // computation.
1538 versioned_handle.version = next_handle_value_ - 1;
1539 }
1540
1541 return versioned_handle;
1542}

1544VersionedComputationHandle UserComputation::GetVersionedHandleAtOperation(
1545 const ComputationDataHandle& operation) const {
1546 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
1547
1548 // The version at which an operation was added is simply the handle value of
1549 // the ComputationDataHandle.
1550 VersionedComputationHandle versioned_handle;
1551 versioned_handle.handle = session_computation_.computation_handle();
1552 versioned_handle.version = operation.handle();
1553 return versioned_handle;
1554}

1557 return GetVersionedHandle().version;
1558}

1560namespace {
1561
1562// Returns true if the operation type corresponding to the given opcase can be
1563// the root of the computation.
1564bool CanBeRoot(const OpRequest::OpCase& op_case) {
1565 switch (op_case) {
1566 case OpRequest::kTraceRequest:
1567 case OpRequest::kSendRequest:
1568 case OpRequest::kOutfeedRequest:
1569 return false;
1570 default:
1571 return true;
1572 }
1573}
1574
1575// Returns a pointer to the operation with the given data handle value in the
1576// given SessionComputation.
1577StatusOr<const OperationRequest*> LookUpRequest(
1578 int64 handle_value, const SessionComputation& session_computation) {
1579 if (session_computation.requests().count(handle_value) == 0) {
1580 return InvalidArgument("no ComputationDataHandle value %lld", handle_value);
1581 }
1582 return &session_computation.requests().at(handle_value);
1583}
1584
1585// Returns the OperationRequest corresponding to the root (result) of the
1586// session computation.
1587StatusOr<const OperationRequest*> GetRoot(
1588 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version,
1589 const SessionComputation& session_computation) {
1590 TF_RET_CHECK(version > 0);
1591 // Not all instructions can be roots. Walk backwards from the operation
1592 // indicated by this version until a valid root is found.
1593 const OperationRequest* root_request = nullptr;
1594 while (version > 0) {
1595 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(root_request,
1596 LookUpRequest(version, session_computation));
1597 if (CanBeRoot(root_request->request().op_case())) {
1598 break;
1599 }
1600 version--;
1601 }
1602 if (version == 0) {
1603 return InternalError("Computation contains no root operation");
1604 }
1605 return root_request;
1606}
1607
1608} // namespace
1609
1610StatusOr<std::shared_ptr<const ProgramShape>>
1611UserComputation::ComputeProgramShape(
1612 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version) const {
1613 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
1614
1615 TF_RET_CHECK(version > 0 && version < next_handle_value_);
1616
1617 if (program_shape_ == nullptr || program_shape_version_ != version) {
1618 // ProgramShape has not been computed yet, or is for different
1619 // version. Compute it now.
1620 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(CheckParametersAreContiguous(version));
1621
1622 auto program_shape = MakeUnique<ProgramShape>();
1623 for (int64 request_num = 1; request_num <= version; ++request_num) {
1624 const OperationRequest& request =
1625 session_computation_.requests().at(request_num);
1626 if (request.request().op_case() == OpRequest::kParameterRequest) {
1627 const ParameterRequest& parameter_request =
1628 request.request().parameter_request();
1629 int64 param_no = parameter_request.parameter();
1630 // Parameters may be out of order so expand ProgramShape parameters
1631 // until it is at least large enough to hold the current parameter
1632 // number.
1633 while (program_shape->parameters_size() <= param_no) {
1634 program_shape->add_parameters();
1635 program_shape->add_parameter_names();
1636 }
1637 *program_shape->mutable_parameters(param_no) = request.output_shape();
1638 *program_shape->mutable_parameter_names(param_no) =
1639 parameter_request.name();
1640 }
1641 }
1642
1643 // The root determines the output shape.
1644 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* root_request,
1645 GetRoot(version, session_computation_));
1646 *program_shape->mutable_result() = root_request->output_shape();
1647 if (ShapeUtil::IsOpaque(program_shape->result())) {
1648 return Unimplemented("Computation results cannot be opaque");
1649 }
1650
1651 program_shape_ = std::move(program_shape);
1652 program_shape_version_ = version;
1653 }
1654
1655 return program_shape_;
1656}

1658namespace {
1659
1660// A visitor which checks whether an operation is pure functional meaning that
1661// it doesn't depend on any parameter with an index higher then num_parameters.
1662// The visitor walks the computation starting at a given operation and sets
1663// is_functional to false iff a parameter or RNG operation is encountered.
1664void PureFunctionalVisitor(const SessionComputation& session_computation,
1665 const ComputationDataHandle& handle,
1666 int64 num_parameters, std::set<int64>* visited,
1667 bool* is_functional) {
1668 if (visited->count(handle.handle()) != 0 || !*is_functional) {
1669 return;
1670 }
1671
1672 const OperationRequest& request =
1673 session_computation.requests().at(handle.handle());
1674 switch (request.request().op_case()) {
1675 case OpRequest::kRngRequest:
1676 *is_functional = false;
1677 break;
1678
1679 case OpRequest::kConstantRequest:
1680 break;
1681
1682 case OpRequest::kGetTupleElementRequest: {
1683 const GetTupleElementRequest& get_tuple_element_request =
1684 request.request().get_tuple_element_request();
1685 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1686 get_tuple_element_request.operand(), num_parameters,
1687 visited, is_functional);
1688 break;
1689 }
1690
1691 case OpRequest::kSliceRequest: {
1692 const SliceRequest& slice_request = request.request().slice_request();
1693 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, slice_request.operand(),
1694 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1695 break;
1696 }
1697
1698 case OpRequest::kDynamicSliceRequest: {
1699 const DynamicSliceRequest& dynamic_slice_request =
1700 request.request().dynamic_slice_request();
1701 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1702 dynamic_slice_request.operand(), num_parameters,
1703 visited, is_functional);
1704 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1705 dynamic_slice_request.start_indices(),
1706 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1707 break;
1708 }
1709
1710 case OpRequest::kDynamicUpdateSliceRequest: {
1711 const DynamicUpdateSliceRequest& dynamic_update_slice_request =
1712 request.request().dynamic_update_slice_request();
1713 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1714 dynamic_update_slice_request.operand(),
1715 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1716 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1717 dynamic_update_slice_request.update(),
1718 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1719 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1720 dynamic_update_slice_request.start_indices(),
1721 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1722 break;
1723 }
1724
1725 case OpRequest::kConcatenateRequest: {
1726 const ConcatenateRequest& concatenate_request =
1727 request.request().concatenate_request();
1728 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle :
1729 concatenate_request.operands()) {
1730 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, handle, num_parameters,
1731 visited, is_functional);
1732 }
1733 break;
1734 }
1735
1736 case OpRequest::kConvolveRequest: {
1737 const ConvolveRequest& convolve_request =
1738 request.request().convolve_request();
1739 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, convolve_request.lhs(),
1740 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1741 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, convolve_request.rhs(),
1742 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1743 break;
1744 }
1745
1746 case OpRequest::kFftRequest: {
1747 const FftRequest& fft_request = request.request().fft_request();
1748 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, fft_request.operand(),
1749 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1750 break;
1751 }
1752
1753 case OpRequest::kCrossReplicaSumRequest: {
1754 // TODO(b/33009255): Implmement constant folding for cross replica sum.
1755 *is_functional = false;
1756 break;
1757 }
1758
1759 case OpRequest::kInfeedRequest: {
1760 *is_functional = false;
1761 break;
1762 }
1763
1764 case OpRequest::kOutfeedRequest: {
1765 *is_functional = false;
1766 break;
1767 }
1768
1769 case OpRequest::kHostComputeRequest: {
1770 *is_functional = false;
1771 break;
1772 }
1773
1774 case OpRequest::kCallRequest: {
1775 const CallRequest& call_request = request.request().call_request();
1776 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle : call_request.operands()) {
1777 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, handle, num_parameters,
1778 visited, is_functional);
1779 }
1780 // TODO(b/32495713): We aren't checking the to_apply computation itself,
1781 // so we conservatively say that computations containing the Call op
1782 // cannot be constant. We cannot set is_functional=false in other similar
1783 // cases since we're already relying on IsConstant to return true.
1784 *is_functional = false;
1785 break;
1786 }
1787
1788 case OpRequest::kCustomCallRequest: {
1789 *is_functional = false;
1790 break;
1791 }
1792
1793 case OpRequest::kDotRequest: {
1794 const DotRequest& dot_request = request.request().dot_request();
1795 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, dot_request.lhs(),
1796 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1797 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, dot_request.rhs(),
1798 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1799 break;
1800 }
1801
1802 case OpRequest::kSendRequest: {
1803 *is_functional = false;
1804 break;
1805 }
1806
1807 case OpRequest::kRecvRequest: {
1808 *is_functional = false;
1809 break;
1810 }
1811
1812 case OpRequest::kMapRequest: {
1813 const MapRequest& map_request = request.request().map_request();
1814 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle : map_request.operands()) {
1815 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, handle, num_parameters,
1816 visited, is_functional);
1817 }
1818 // TODO(b/32495713): We aren't checking the to_apply computation itself.
1819 break;
1820 }
1821
1822 case OpRequest::kReduceRequest: {
1823 const ReduceRequest& reduce_request = request.request().reduce_request();
1824 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, reduce_request.operand(),
1825 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1826 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, reduce_request.init_value(),
1827 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1828 // TODO(b/32495713): We aren't checking the to_apply computation itself.
1829 break;
1830 }
1831
1832 case OpRequest::kReduceWindowRequest: {
1833 const ReduceWindowRequest& reduce_window_request =
1834 request.request().reduce_window_request();
1835 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1836 reduce_window_request.operand(), num_parameters,
1837 visited, is_functional);
1838 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1839 reduce_window_request.init_value(), num_parameters,
1840 visited, is_functional);
1841 // TODO(b/32495713): We aren't checking the to_apply computation itself.
1842 break;
1843 }
1844
1845 case OpRequest::kSelectAndScatterRequest: {
1846 const SelectAndScatterRequest& select_and_scatter_request =
1847 request.request().select_and_scatter_request();
1848 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1849 select_and_scatter_request.operand(),
1850 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1851 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1852 select_and_scatter_request.source(), num_parameters,
1853 visited, is_functional);
1854 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1855 select_and_scatter_request.init_value(),
1856 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1857 // TODO(b/32495713): We aren't checking the select and scatter
1858 // computations themselves.
1859 break;
1860 }
1861
1862 case OpRequest::kBroadcastRequest: {
1863 const BroadcastRequest& broadcast_request =
1864 request.request().broadcast_request();
1865 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, broadcast_request.operand(),
1866 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1867 break;
1868 }
1869
1870 case OpRequest::kReshapeRequest: {
1871 const ReshapeRequest& reshape_request =
1872 request.request().reshape_request();
1873 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, reshape_request.operand(),
1874 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1875 break;
1876 }
1877
1878 case OpRequest::kReverseRequest: {
1879 const ReverseRequest& reverse_request =
1880 request.request().reverse_request();
1881 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, reverse_request.operand(),
1882 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1883 break;
1884 }
1885
1886 case OpRequest::kPadRequest: {
1887 const PadRequest& pad_request = request.request().pad_request();
1888 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, pad_request.operand(),
1889 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1890 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, pad_request.padding_value(),
1891 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1892 break;
1893 }
1894
1895 case OpRequest::kParameterRequest: {
1896 const ParameterRequest& parameter_request =
1897 request.request().parameter_request();
1898 if (parameter_request.parameter() >= num_parameters) {
1899 *is_functional = false;
1900 }
1901 break;
1902 }
1903
1904 case OpRequest::kConvertRequest: {
1905 const ConvertRequest& convert_request =
1906 request.request().convert_request();
1907 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, convert_request.operand(),
1908 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1909 break;
1910 }
1911
1912 case OpRequest::kBitcastConvertRequest: {
1913 const ConvertRequest& convert_request =
1914 request.request().bitcast_convert_request();
1915 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, convert_request.operand(),
1916 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1917 break;
1918 }
1919
1920 case OpRequest::kWhileRequest: {
1921 const WhileRequest& while_request = request.request().while_request();
1922 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, while_request.init(),
1923 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1924 // TODO(b/32495713): We aren't checking the condition and body
1925 // computations themselves.
1926 *is_functional = false;
1927 break;
1928 }
1929
1930 case OpRequest::kConditionalRequest: {
1931 const ConditionalRequest& conditional_request =
1932 request.request().conditional_request();
1933 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1934 conditional_request.predicate(), num_parameters,
1935 visited, is_functional);
1936 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1937 conditional_request.true_operand(), num_parameters,
1938 visited, is_functional);
1939 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1940 conditional_request.false_operand(), num_parameters,
1941 visited, is_functional);
1942 // TODO(b/32495713): We aren't checking the true and false computations
1943 // themselves.
1944 break;
1945 }
1946
1947 case OpRequest::kTernaryOpRequest: {
1948 const TernaryOpRequest& ternary_op_request =
1949 request.request().ternary_op_request();
1950 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, ternary_op_request.lhs(),
1951 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1952 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, ternary_op_request.rhs(),
1953 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1954 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, ternary_op_request.ehs(),
1955 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1956 break;
1957 }
1958
1959 case OpRequest::kTransposeRequest: {
1960 const TransposeRequest& transpose_request =
1961 request.request().transpose_request();
1962 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, transpose_request.operand(),
1963 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1964 break;
1965 }
1966
1967 case OpRequest::kVariadicOpRequest: {
1968 const VariadicOpRequest& variadic_op_request =
1969 request.request().variadic_op_request();
1970 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle :
1971 variadic_op_request.operands()) {
1972 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, handle, num_parameters,
1973 visited, is_functional);
1974 }
1975 break;
1976 }
1977
1978 case OpRequest::kUnaryOpRequest: {
1979 const UnaryOpRequest& unary_op_request =
1980 request.request().unary_op_request();
1981 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, unary_op_request.operand(),
1982 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1983 break;
1984 }
1985
1986 case OpRequest::kBatchNormTrainingRequest: {
1987 const BatchNormTrainingRequest& batch_norm_training_request =
1988 request.request().batch_norm_training_request();
1989 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1990 batch_norm_training_request.operand(),
1991 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1992 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1993 batch_norm_training_request.scale(), num_parameters,
1994 visited, is_functional);
1995 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
1996 batch_norm_training_request.offset(),
1997 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
1998 break;
1999 }
2000
2001 case OpRequest::kBatchNormInferenceRequest: {
2002 const BatchNormInferenceRequest& batch_norm_inference_request =
2003 request.request().batch_norm_inference_request();
2004 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2005 batch_norm_inference_request.operand(),
2006 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2007 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2008 batch_norm_inference_request.scale(),
2009 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2010 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2011 batch_norm_inference_request.offset(),
2012 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2013 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2014 batch_norm_inference_request.mean(), num_parameters,
2015 visited, is_functional);
2016 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2017 batch_norm_inference_request.variance(),
2018 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2019 break;
2020 }
2021
2022 case OpRequest::kBatchNormGradRequest: {
2023 const BatchNormGradRequest& batch_norm_grad_request =
2024 request.request().batch_norm_grad_request();
2025 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2026 batch_norm_grad_request.operand(), num_parameters,
2027 visited, is_functional);
2028 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2029 batch_norm_grad_request.scale(), num_parameters,
2030 visited, is_functional);
2031 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, batch_norm_grad_request.mean(),
2032 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2033 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2034 batch_norm_grad_request.variance(), num_parameters,
2035 visited, is_functional);
2036 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2037 batch_norm_grad_request.grad_output(),
2038 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2039 break;
2040 }
2041
2042 case OpRequest::kBinaryOpRequest: {
2043 const BinaryOpRequest& binary_op_request =
2044 request.request().binary_op_request();
2045 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, binary_op_request.lhs(),
2046 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2047 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation, binary_op_request.rhs(),
2048 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2049 break;
2050 }
2051
2052 case OpRequest::kGatherRequest: {
2053 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2054 request.request().gather_request().input(),
2055 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2056 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation,
2057 request.request().gather_request().gather_indices(),
2058 num_parameters, visited, is_functional);
2059 break;
2060 }
2061
2062 case OpRequest::OP_NOT_SET:
2063 LOG(FATAL) << "OperationRequest doesn't contain a request";
2064
2065 default:
2066 LOG(FATAL) << "Unexpected request type: " << request.request().op_case();
2067 }
2068 if (!*is_functional) {
2069 VLOG(1) << "Non-functional: " << request.request().DebugString();
2070 }
2071 visited->insert(handle.handle());
2072}

2074} // namespace
2075
2076StatusOr<bool> UserComputation::IsConstant(const ComputationDataHandle& handle,
2077 int64 num_parameters) {
2078 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
2079
2080 // Verify that the handle is valid.
2081 auto operation_status = LookUpRequest(handle);
2082 if (!operation_status.ok()) {
2083 return operation_status.status();
2084 }
2085
2086 bool is_constant = true;
2087 std::set<int64> visited;
2088 PureFunctionalVisitor(session_computation_, handle, num_parameters, &visited,
2089 &is_constant);
2090
2091 return is_constant;
2092}

2094std::vector<VersionedComputationHandle>
2095UserComputation::GetEmbeddedComputations(
2096 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version) const {
2097 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
2098
2099 VLOG(1)
2100 << "GetEmbeddedComputations(" << name() << " "
2101 << VersionedComputationHandle{session_computation_.computation_handle(),
2102 version}
2103 << ")";
2104 XLA_VLOG_LINES(3, session_computation_.DebugString());
2105
2106 std::vector<VersionedComputationHandle> computations;
2107 std::vector<int64> sorted_handles;
2108 for (const auto& handle_request : session_computation_.requests()) {
2109 sorted_handles.push_back(handle_request.first);
2110 }
2111 std::sort(sorted_handles.begin(), sorted_handles.end());
2112 for (int64 handle : sorted_handles) {
2113 const auto& handle_request = session_computation_.requests().find(handle);
2114 CHECK(handle_request != session_computation_.requests().end());
2115 int64 handle_value = handle_request->first;
2116 if (handle_value <= version) {
2117 const OperationRequest& request = handle_request->second;
2118 switch (request.request().op_case()) {
2119 case OpRequest::kCallRequest: {
2120 CHECK_EQ(1, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2121 const CallRequest& call_request = request.request().call_request();
2122 const VersionedComputationHandle versioned_handle = {
2123 call_request.to_apply(),
2124 request.embedded_computation_versions(0)};
2125 computations.push_back(versioned_handle);
2126 break;
2127 }
2128
2129 case OpRequest::kMapRequest: {
2130 CHECK_EQ(1, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2131 const MapRequest& map_request = request.request().map_request();
2132 const VersionedComputationHandle versioned_handle = {
2133 map_request.to_apply(), request.embedded_computation_versions(0)};
2134 computations.push_back(versioned_handle);
2135 break;
2136 }
2137
2138 case OpRequest::kReduceRequest: {
2139 CHECK_EQ(1, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2140 const ReduceRequest& reduce_request =
2141 request.request().reduce_request();
2142 const VersionedComputationHandle versioned_handle = {
2143 reduce_request.to_apply(),
2144 request.embedded_computation_versions(0)};
2145 computations.push_back(versioned_handle);
2146 break;
2147 }
2148
2149 case OpRequest::kReduceWindowRequest: {
2150 CHECK_EQ(1, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2151 const ReduceWindowRequest& reduce_window_request =
2152 request.request().reduce_window_request();
2153 const VersionedComputationHandle versioned_handle = {
2154 reduce_window_request.to_apply(),
2155 request.embedded_computation_versions(0)};
2156 computations.push_back(versioned_handle);
2157 break;
2158 }
2159
2160 case OpRequest::kSelectAndScatterRequest: {
2161 CHECK_EQ(2, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2162 const SelectAndScatterRequest& select_and_scatter_request =
2163 request.request().select_and_scatter_request();
2164 const VersionedComputationHandle select_versioned_handle = {
2165 select_and_scatter_request.select(),
2166 request.embedded_computation_versions(0)};
2167 computations.push_back(select_versioned_handle);
2168 const VersionedComputationHandle scatter_versioned_handle = {
2169 select_and_scatter_request.scatter(),
2170 request.embedded_computation_versions(1)};
2171 computations.push_back(scatter_versioned_handle);
2172 break;
2173 }
2174
2175 case OpRequest::kWhileRequest: {
2176 CHECK_EQ(2, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2177 const WhileRequest& while_request = request.request().while_request();
2178 const VersionedComputationHandle condition_versioned_handle = {
2179 while_request.condition(),
2180 request.embedded_computation_versions(0)};
2181 computations.push_back(condition_versioned_handle);
2182 const VersionedComputationHandle body_versioned_handle = {
2183 while_request.body(), request.embedded_computation_versions(1)};
2184 computations.push_back(body_versioned_handle);
2185 break;
2186 }
2187
2188 case OpRequest::kConditionalRequest: {
2189 CHECK_EQ(2, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2190 const ConditionalRequest& conditional_request =
2191 request.request().conditional_request();
2192 const VersionedComputationHandle true_computation_versioned_handle = {
2193 conditional_request.true_computation(),
2194 request.embedded_computation_versions(0)};
2195 computations.push_back(true_computation_versioned_handle);
2196 const VersionedComputationHandle false_computation_versioned_handle =
2197 {conditional_request.false_computation(),
2198 request.embedded_computation_versions(1)};
2199 computations.push_back(false_computation_versioned_handle);
2200 break;
2201 }
2202
2203 default:
2204 // No embedded computation.
2205 break;
2206 }
2207 }
2208 }
2209 VLOG(2) << "Embedded computations: "
2210 << tensorflow::str_util::Join(
2211 computations, ", ",
2212 [](string* out, const VersionedComputationHandle& h) {
2213 out->append(h.ToString());
2214 });
2215 return computations;
2216}

2236Status UserComputation::RemapEmbeddedComputations(
2237 const std::map<int64, ComputationHandle>& old_to_new) {
2238 auto update = [&old_to_new](ComputationHandle* to_update) -> Status {
2239 int64 old = to_update->handle();
2240 auto it = old_to_new.find(old);
2241 if (it == old_to_new.end()) {
2242 string mapping = tensorflow::str_util::Join(
2243 old_to_new, ", ",
2244 [](string* out, std::pair<int64, ComputationHandle> element) {
2245 tensorflow::strings::Appendf(out, "%lld:%lld", element.first,
2246 element.second.handle());
2247 });
2248 return NotFound(
2249 "could not find referenced (old) computation handle in mapping: "
2250 "%lld; mapping: {%s}",
2251 old, mapping.c_str());
2252 }
2253 VLOG(2) << "remapping " << old << " to " << it->second.handle();
2254 *to_update = it->second;
2255 return Status::OK();
2256 };
2257 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(update(session_computation_.mutable_computation_handle()));
2258 for (auto& handle_request : *session_computation_.mutable_requests()) {
2259 OperationRequest& request = handle_request.second;
2260 switch (request.request().op_case()) {
2261 case OpRequest::kCallRequest: {
2262 TF_RET_CHECK(1 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2263 CallRequest* call_request =
2264 request.mutable_request()->mutable_call_request();
2265 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(update(call_request->mutable_to_apply()));
2266 break;
2267 }
2268 case OpRequest::kMapRequest: {
2269 TF_RET_CHECK(1 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2270 MapRequest* map_request =
2271 request.mutable_request()->mutable_map_request();
2272 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(update(map_request->mutable_to_apply()));
2273 break;
2274 }
2275 case OpRequest::kReduceRequest: {
2276 TF_RET_CHECK(1 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2277 ReduceRequest* reduce_request =
2278 request.mutable_request()->mutable_reduce_request();
2279 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(update(reduce_request->mutable_to_apply()));
2280 break;
2281 }
2282 case OpRequest::kReduceWindowRequest: {
2283 TF_RET_CHECK(1 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2284 ReduceWindowRequest* reduce_window_request =
2285 request.mutable_request()->mutable_reduce_window_request();
2286 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(update(reduce_window_request->mutable_to_apply()));
2287 break;
2288 }
2289 case OpRequest::kSelectAndScatterRequest: {
2290 TF_RET_CHECK(2 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2291 SelectAndScatterRequest* select_and_scatter_request =
2292 request.mutable_request()->mutable_select_and_scatter_request();
2293 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2294 update(select_and_scatter_request->mutable_select()));
2295 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2296 update(select_and_scatter_request->mutable_scatter()));
2297 break;
2298 }
2299 case OpRequest::kWhileRequest: {
2300 TF_RET_CHECK(2 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2301 WhileRequest* while_request =
2302 request.mutable_request()->mutable_while_request();
2303 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(update(while_request->mutable_condition()));
2304 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(update(while_request->mutable_body()));
2305 break;
2306 }
2307 case OpRequest::kConditionalRequest: {
2308 TF_RET_CHECK(2 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2309 ConditionalRequest* conditional_request =
2310 request.mutable_request()->mutable_conditional_request();
2311 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2312 update(conditional_request->mutable_true_computation()));
2313 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2314 update(conditional_request->mutable_false_computation()));
2315 break;
2316 }
2317 default:
2318 // No embedded computation.
2319 TF_RET_CHECK(0 == request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
2320 break;
2321 }
2322 }
2323 return Status::OK();
2324}
2325
2326SessionComputation UserComputation::CloneSessionComputation(
2327 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version) const {
2328 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
2329 SessionComputation result = session_computation_;
2330 // Erase all the requests that exceed the version specified.
2331 // There's no lower_bound method on tensorflow::protobuf::Map so we iterate
2332 // all the elements.
2333 auto it = result.mutable_requests()->begin();
2334 while (it != result.mutable_requests()->end()) {
2335 if (it->first > version) {
2336 it = result.mutable_requests()->erase(it);
2337 } else {
2338 ++it;
2339 }
2340 }
2341 return result;
2342}
2343
2344StatusOr<const OperationRequest*> UserComputation::LookUpRequest(
2345 const ComputationDataHandle& handle) const {
2346 int64 handle_value = handle.handle();
2347 if (session_computation_.requests().count(handle_value) == 0) {
2348 return InvalidArgument("no ComputationDataHandle value %lld", handle_value);
2349 }
2350 return &session_computation_.requests().at(handle_value);
2351}
2352
2353Status UserComputation::CheckParametersAreContiguous(
2354 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version) const {
2355 TF_RET_CHECK(version > 0 && version < next_handle_value_);
2356
2357 // Determine number of parameter inputs at the given version.
2358 std::map<int64, const ParameterRequest*> parameter_requests;
2359 for (int64 request_num = 1; request_num <= version; ++request_num) {
2360 const OperationRequest& request =
2361 session_computation_.requests().at(request_num);
2362
2363 if (request.request().op_case() == OpRequest::kParameterRequest) {
2364 const ParameterRequest& parameter_request =
2365 request.request().parameter_request();
2366 // Duplicate parameters should be checked when parameter requests are
2367 // added.
2368 TF_RET_CHECK(0 ==
2369 parameter_requests.count(parameter_request.parameter()));
2370 parameter_requests[parameter_request.parameter()] = &parameter_request;
2371 }
2372 }
2373
2374 for (int64 i = 0; i < parameter_requests.size(); ++i) {
2375 auto it = parameter_requests.find(i);
2376 if (it == parameter_requests.end()) {
2377 return FailedPrecondition(
2378 "computation %s does not have all its parameters populated "
2379 "sequentially, missing parameter %lld",
2380 name_.c_str(), i);
2381 }
2382 }
2383
2384 return Status::OK();
2385}

2389// Helper class which builds an HLO computation from a SessionComputation. To
2390// construct the HLO computation, the SessionComputation graph is walked in
2391// DFS order lowering each OperationRequest to an HLO instruction.
2392class ComputationLowerer {
2393 public:
2394 static StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<HloComputation>> Lower(
2395 const string& computation_name,
2396 const SessionComputation& session_computation,
2397 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version,
2398 UserComputation::HloComputationResolver hlo_resolver,
2399 const DebugOptions& debug_options,
2400 bool include_unreachable_instructions) {
2401 ComputationLowerer lowerer(computation_name, session_computation, version,
2402 std::move(hlo_resolver), debug_options,
2403 include_unreachable_instructions);
2404 return lowerer.Lower();
2405 }
2406
2407 private:
2408 ComputationLowerer(const string& computation_name,
2409 const SessionComputation& session_computation,
2410 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version,
2411 UserComputation::HloComputationResolver hlo_resolver,
2412 const DebugOptions& debug_options,
2413 bool include_unreachable_instructions)
2414 : hlo_builder_(computation_name),
2415 session_computation_(session_computation),
2416 version_(version),
2417 hlo_resolver_(std::move(hlo_resolver)),
2418 debug_options_(debug_options),
2419 include_unreachable_instructions_(include_unreachable_instructions) {}
2420
2421 // Build an HLO computation from the SessionComputation at the given
2422 // version.
2423 StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<HloComputation>> Lower();
2424
2425 private:
2426 // Traverses the computation 'root' using a DFS, calling 'visit' in postorder.
2427 void TraversePostorder(
2428 const ComputationDataHandle& root,
2429 std::unordered_map<int64, HloInstruction*>* visited,
2430 const std::function<void(const ComputationDataHandle&)>& visit);
2431
2432 // DFS visitor of the UserComputation operations which lowers the operations
2433 // to HLO instructions.
2434 void Visit(const ComputationDataHandle& handle,
2435 std::unordered_map<int64, HloInstruction*>* instructions);
2436
2437 // Resolves a ComputationHandle and Version to a previously lowered
2438 // HloComputation using the hlo_resolver_ function.
2439 HloComputation* ResolveComputation(
2440 const ComputationHandle& handle,
2441 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version);
2442
2443 // This function takes an input value which is being implicitly broadcast into
2444 // an output shape and figures out the right kBroadcast instruction(s)
2445 // necessary to replicate the implicit broadcast semantics explicitly.
2446 HloInstruction* ImplicitBroadcastToExplicitBroadcast(
2447 HloInstruction* operand, const Shape& output_shape);
2448
2449 HloComputation::Builder hlo_builder_;
2450 const SessionComputation& session_computation_;
2451 const VersionedComputationHandle::Version version_;
2452 const UserComputation::HloComputationResolver hlo_resolver_;
2453 const DebugOptions& debug_options_;
2454 const bool include_unreachable_instructions_;
2455};
2456
2457// Calls 'apply' on each operand of 'request'.
2458static void ForEachOperand(
2459 const OperationRequest& request,
2460 const std::function<void(const ComputationDataHandle& param)>& apply) {
2461 switch (request.request().op_case()) {
2462 case OpRequest::kRngRequest: {
2463 const RngRequest& rng_request = request.request().rng_request();
2464 for (const ComputationDataHandle& param : rng_request.parameter()) {
2465 apply(param);
2466 }
2467 break;
2468 }
2469
2470 case OpRequest::kConstantRequest:
2471 break;
2472 case OpRequest::kGetTupleElementRequest: {
2473 const GetTupleElementRequest& get_tuple_element_request =
2474 request.request().get_tuple_element_request();
2475 apply(get_tuple_element_request.operand());
2476 break;
2477 }
2478
2479 case OpRequest::kSliceRequest: {
2480 const SliceRequest& slice_request = request.request().slice_request();
2481 apply(slice_request.operand());
2482 break;
2483 }
2484
2485 case OpRequest::kDynamicSliceRequest: {
2486 const DynamicSliceRequest& dynamic_slice_request =
2487 request.request().dynamic_slice_request();
2488 apply(dynamic_slice_request.operand());
2489 apply(dynamic_slice_request.start_indices());
2490 break;
2491 }
2492
2493 case OpRequest::kDynamicUpdateSliceRequest: {
2494 const DynamicUpdateSliceRequest& dynamic_update_slice_request =
2495 request.request().dynamic_update_slice_request();
2496 apply(dynamic_update_slice_request.operand());
2497 apply(dynamic_update_slice_request.update());
2498 apply(dynamic_update_slice_request.start_indices());
2499 break;
2500 }
2501
2502 case OpRequest::kConcatenateRequest: {
2503 const ConcatenateRequest& concatenate_request =
2504 request.request().concatenate_request();
2505 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle :
2506 concatenate_request.operands()) {
2507 apply(handle);
2508 }
2509 break;
2510 }
2511
2512 case OpRequest::kConvolveRequest: {
2513 const ConvolveRequest& convolve_request =
2514 request.request().convolve_request();
2515 apply(convolve_request.lhs());
2516 apply(convolve_request.rhs());
2517 break;
2518 }
2519
2520 case OpRequest::kFftRequest: {
2521 const FftRequest& fft_request = request.request().fft_request();
2522 apply(fft_request.operand());
2523 break;
2524 }
2525
2526 case OpRequest::kBatchNormTrainingRequest: {
2527 const BatchNormTrainingRequest& batch_norm_training_request =
2528 request.request().batch_norm_training_request();
2529
2530 apply(batch_norm_training_request.operand());
2531 apply(batch_norm_training_request.scale());
2532 apply(batch_norm_training_request.offset());
2533 break;
2534 }
2535
2536 case OpRequest::kBatchNormInferenceRequest: {
2537 const BatchNormInferenceRequest& batch_norm_inference_request =
2538 request.request().batch_norm_inference_request();
2539
2540 apply(batch_norm_inference_request.operand());
2541 apply(batch_norm_inference_request.scale());
2542 apply(batch_norm_inference_request.offset());
2543 apply(batch_norm_inference_request.mean());
2544 apply(batch_norm_inference_request.variance());
2545 break;
2546 }
2547
2548 case OpRequest::kBatchNormGradRequest: {
2549 const BatchNormGradRequest& batch_norm_grad_request =
2550 request.request().batch_norm_grad_request();
2551
2552 apply(batch_norm_grad_request.operand());
2553 apply(batch_norm_grad_request.scale());
2554 apply(batch_norm_grad_request.mean());

2778
2779void ComputationLowerer::TraversePostorder(
2780 const ComputationDataHandle& root,
2781 std::unordered_map<int64, HloInstruction*>* visited,
2782 const std::function<void(const ComputationDataHandle&)>& visit) {
2783 // Stack containing {handle, enter} pairs. The 'enter' value describes whether
2784 // we are entering or leaving 'handle'.
2785 std::stack<std::pair<ComputationDataHandle, bool>> work;
2786 work.push({root, true});
2787 while (!work.empty()) {
2788 ComputationDataHandle handle;
2789 bool enter;
2790 std::tie(handle, enter) = work.top();
2791 work.pop();
2792
2793 if (enter) {
2794 // We are entering 'handle'. The first time we enter 'handle', we add it
2795 // to 'visited' with a nullptr value. If 'handle' is already in 'visited',
2796 // we do not visit it again. This algorithm only uses the presence of
2797 // a handle in 'visited', but we use a map so we can use the same data
2798 // structure to store the HloInstruction outputs.
2799 if (visited->emplace(handle.handle(), nullptr).second) {
2800 const OperationRequest& request =
2801 session_computation_.requests().at(handle.handle());
2802 // Push the corresponding 'leave' action onto the stack, followed by
2803 // the operands.
2804 work.push({handle, false});
2805 ForEachOperand(request, [&work](const ComputationDataHandle& child) {
2806 work.push({child, true});
2807 });
2808 }
2809 } else {
2810 // We are leaving 'handle'. We have visited the operands of 'handle', and
2811 // now can visit the 'handle' itself.
2812 visit(handle);
2813 }
2814 }
2815}
2816
2817StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<HloComputation>> ComputationLowerer::Lower() {
2818 // Map from ComputationDataHandle to HLO instruction. Serves as a record of
2819 // which operations have been visited as well as a cache for looking up
2820 // ComputationDataHandles as HloInstructions.
2821 std::unordered_map<int64, HloInstruction*> instructions;
2822
2823 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* root_request,
2824 GetRoot(version_, session_computation_));
2825
2826 auto visit = [&](const ComputationDataHandle& handle) {
2827 Visit(handle, &instructions);
2828 };
2829 TraversePostorder(root_request->output_handle(), &instructions, visit);
2830 HloInstruction* hlo_root =
2831 instructions.at(root_request->output_handle().handle());
2832
2833 if (include_unreachable_instructions_) {
2834 // Iterate through all computation data handles, and visit any unvisited
2835 // operations.
2836 for (int64 request_num = 1; request_num <= version_; ++request_num) {
2837 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(const OperationRequest* request,
2838 LookUpRequest(request_num, session_computation_));
2839 TraversePostorder(request->output_handle(), &instructions, visit);
2840 }
2841 }
2842
2843 return hlo_builder_.Build(hlo_root);
2844}
2845
2846HloComputation* ComputationLowerer::ResolveComputation(
2847 const ComputationHandle& handle,
2848 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version) {
2849 const VersionedComputationHandle checked_handle = {handle, version};
2850 return hlo_resolver_(checked_handle);
2851}
2852
2853HloInstruction* ComputationLowerer::ImplicitBroadcastToExplicitBroadcast(
2854 HloInstruction* operand, const Shape& output_shape) {
2855 auto fadd = [this](std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> x) {
2856 return hlo_builder_.AddInstruction(std::move(x));
2857 };
2858 return fadd(
2859 HloInstruction::CreateBroadcastSequence(output_shape, operand, fadd));
2860}
2861
2862void ComputationLowerer::Visit(
2863 const ComputationDataHandle& handle,
2864 std::unordered_map<int64, HloInstruction*>* instructions) {
2865 CHECK_LE(handle.handle(), version_);
2866 CHECK(instructions->at(handle.handle()) == nullptr);
2867 const OperationRequest& request =
2868 session_computation_.requests().at(handle.handle());
2869 auto add_instruction = [&](std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> instruction) {
2870 HloInstruction* hlo_instruction =
2871 hlo_builder_.AddInstruction(std::move(instruction));
2872 hlo_instruction->set_metadata(request.request().metadata());
2873 if (request.request().has_sharding()) {
2874 OpSharding op_sharding = request.request().sharding();
2875 hlo_instruction->set_sharding(
2876 HloSharding::FromProto(op_sharding).ValueOrDie());
2877 }
2878 return hlo_instruction;
2879 };
2880 auto lookup_instruction = [&](const ComputationDataHandle& handle) {
2881 return instructions->at(handle.handle());
2882 };
2883 HloInstruction* hlo_instruction;
2884 switch (request.request().op_case()) {
2885 case OpRequest::kRngRequest: {
2886 const RngRequest& rng_request = request.request().rng_request();
2887 std::vector<HloInstruction*> parameters;
2888 for (const ComputationDataHandle& param : rng_request.parameter()) {
2889 parameters.push_back(lookup_instruction(param));
2890 }
2891 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateRng(
2892 request.output_shape(), rng_request.distribution(), parameters));
2893 break;
2894 }
2895
2896 case OpRequest::kConstantRequest: {
2897 const ConstantRequest& constant_request =
2898 request.request().constant_request();
2899 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateConstant(
2900 Literal::CreateFromProto(constant_request.literal())
2901 .ConsumeValueOrDie()));
2902 break;
2903 }
2904
2905 case OpRequest::kGetTupleElementRequest: {
2906 const GetTupleElementRequest& get_tuple_element_request =
2907 request.request().get_tuple_element_request();
2908 HloInstruction* operand =
2909 lookup_instruction(get_tuple_element_request.operand());
2910 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateGetTupleElement(
2911 request.output_shape(), operand, get_tuple_element_request.index()));
2912 break;
2913 }
2914
2915 case OpRequest::kSliceRequest: {
2916 const SliceRequest& slice_request = request.request().slice_request();
2917 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(slice_request.operand());
2918 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateSlice(
2919 request.output_shape(), operand,
2920 AsInt64Slice(slice_request.start_indices()),
2921 AsInt64Slice(slice_request.limit_indices()),
2922 AsInt64Slice(slice_request.strides())));
2923 break;
2924 }
2925
2926 case OpRequest::kDynamicSliceRequest: {
2927 const DynamicSliceRequest& dynamic_slice_request =
2928 request.request().dynamic_slice_request();
2929 HloInstruction* operand =
2930 lookup_instruction(dynamic_slice_request.operand());
2931 HloInstruction* start_indices =
2932 lookup_instruction(dynamic_slice_request.start_indices());
2933
2934 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateDynamicSlice(
2935 request.output_shape(), operand, start_indices,
2936 AsInt64Slice(dynamic_slice_request.slice_sizes())));
2937 break;
2938 }
2939
2940 case OpRequest::kDynamicUpdateSliceRequest: {
2941 const DynamicUpdateSliceRequest& dynamic_update_slice_request =
2942 request.request().dynamic_update_slice_request();
2943 HloInstruction* operand =
2944 lookup_instruction(dynamic_update_slice_request.operand());
2945 HloInstruction* update =
2946 lookup_instruction(dynamic_update_slice_request.update());
2947 HloInstruction* start_indices =
2948 lookup_instruction(dynamic_update_slice_request.start_indices());
2949 hlo_instruction =
2950 add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateDynamicUpdateSlice(
2951 request.output_shape(), operand, update, start_indices));
2952 break;
2953 }

2955 case OpRequest::kConcatenateRequest: {

2959 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle :
2960 concatenate_request.operands()) {
2961 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(handle);
2962 operands.push_back(operand);
2963 }
2964 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateConcatenate(
2965 request.output_shape(), operands, concatenate_request.dimension()));
2966 break;
2967 }

3144 lookup_instruction(batch_norm_grad_request.operand());

3160 case OpRequest::kBroadcastRequest: {
3161 const BroadcastRequest& broadcast_request =
3162 request.request().broadcast_request();
3163 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(broadcast_request.operand());
3164 std::vector<int64> broadcast_dimensions;
3165 // The client-level broadcast instruction just appends dimensions on the
3166 // left (adds lowest numbered dimensions). The HLO broadcast op is more
3167 // flexible and can add new dimensions anywhere. The broadcast_dimensions
3168 // maps operand dimensions to dimensions in the broadcast output, so
3169 // to append dimensions on the left the broadcast_dimensions should just
3170 // be the n highest dimension numbers of the output shape where n is
3171 // the number of input dimensions.
3172 broadcast_dimensions.reserve(ShapeUtil::Rank(operand->shape()));
3173 for (int i = 0; i < ShapeUtil::Rank(operand->shape()); ++i) {
3174 broadcast_dimensions.push_back(i +
3175 ShapeUtil::Rank(request.output_shape()) -
3176 ShapeUtil::Rank(operand->shape()));
3177 }
3178 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateBroadcast(
3179 request.output_shape(), operand, broadcast_dimensions));
3180 break;

3185 request.request().reshape_request();

3187 HloInstruction* transposed;
3188 if (IsIdentityPermutation(AsInt64Slice(reshape_request.dimensions()))) {
3189 transposed = operand;

3191 transposed = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateTranspose(
3192 ShapeUtil::PermuteDimensions(
3193 InversePermutation(AsInt64Slice(reshape_request.dimensions())),
3194 operand->shape()),
3195 operand, AsInt64Slice(reshape_request.dimensions())));
3196 }
3197 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(
3198 HloInstruction::CreateReshape(request.output_shape(), transposed));
3199 break;
3200 }

3202 case OpRequest::kTransposeRequest: {

3204 request.request().transpose_request();
3205 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(transpose_request.operand());
3206 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateTranspose(
3207 ShapeUtil::PermuteDimensions(
3208 InversePermutation(AsInt64Slice(transpose_request.dimensions())),
3209 operand->shape()),
3210 operand, AsInt64Slice(transpose_request.dimensions())));
3211 break;
3212 }

3218 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateReverse(
3219 request.output_shape(), operand,
3220 AsInt64Slice(reverse_request.dimensions())));

3222 }

3239 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateRecvDone(recv));

3254 request.request().convert_request();

3257 HloInstruction::CreateConvert(request.output_shape(), operand));

3261 case OpRequest::kBitcastConvertRequest: {
3262 const ConvertRequest& convert_request =

3264 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(convert_request.operand());
3265 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateBitcastConvert(

3270 case OpRequest::kWhileRequest: {
3271 const WhileRequest& while_request = request.request().while_request();
3272 CHECK_EQ(2, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
3273 VersionedComputationHandle::Version condition_version =
3274 request.embedded_computation_versions(0);

3278 request.embedded_computation_versions(1);

3281 HloInstruction* init = lookup_instruction(while_request.init());
3282 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateWhile(
3283 request.output_shape(), condition, body, init));
3284 break;

3286
3287 case OpRequest::kConditionalRequest: {
3288 const ConditionalRequest& conditional_request =
3289 request.request().conditional_request();
3290 CHECK_EQ(2, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
3291 VersionedComputationHandle::Version true_computation_version =
3292 request.embedded_computation_versions(0);
3293 HloComputation* true_computation = ResolveComputation(
3294 conditional_request.true_computation(), true_computation_version);
3295 VersionedComputationHandle::Version false_computation_version =
3296 request.embedded_computation_versions(1);
3297 HloComputation* false_computation = ResolveComputation(
3298 conditional_request.false_computation(), false_computation_version);
3299 HloInstruction* predicate =
3300 lookup_instruction(conditional_request.predicate());
3301 HloInstruction* true_operand =
3302 lookup_instruction(conditional_request.true_operand());
3303 HloInstruction* false_operand =
3304 lookup_instruction(conditional_request.false_operand());
3305 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateConditional(
3306 request.output_shape(), predicate, true_operand, true_computation,
3307 false_operand, false_computation));
3308 break;
3309 }
3310
3311 case OpRequest::kTernaryOpRequest: {
3312 const TernaryOpRequest& ternary_op_request =
3313 request.request().ternary_op_request();
3314 HloInstruction* lhs = lookup_instruction(ternary_op_request.lhs());
3315 HloInstruction* rhs = lookup_instruction(ternary_op_request.rhs());
3316 HloInstruction* ehs = lookup_instruction(ternary_op_request.ehs());
3317 auto hlo_opcode = TernaryOperationToHloOpcode(ternary_op_request.triop());
3318 if (debug_options_.xla_eliminate_hlo_implicit_broadcast() &&
3319 !ShapeUtil::IsTuple(request.output_shape())) {
3320 if (!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(lhs->shape()) &&
3321 !ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(request.output_shape(), lhs->shape())) {
3322 // lhs side is being implicitly broadcast. Change to explicit.
3323 lhs =
3324 ImplicitBroadcastToExplicitBroadcast(lhs, request.output_shape());
3325 }
3326
3327 if (!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(rhs->shape()) &&
3328 !ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(request.output_shape(), rhs->shape())) {
3329 rhs =
3330 ImplicitBroadcastToExplicitBroadcast(rhs, request.output_shape());
3331 }
3332
3333 if (!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(ehs->shape()) &&
3334 !ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(request.output_shape(), ehs->shape())) {
3335 ehs =
3336 ImplicitBroadcastToExplicitBroadcast(ehs, request.output_shape());
3337 }
3338 }
3339
3340 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateTernary(
3341 request.output_shape(), hlo_opcode, lhs, rhs, ehs));
3342 break;
3343 }

3345 case OpRequest::kVariadicOpRequest: {
3346 const VariadicOpRequest& variadic_op_request =

3350 variadic_op_request.operands()) {
3351 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(handle);

3355 VariadicOperationToHloOpcode(variadic_op_request.varop());

3357 request.output_shape(), hlo_opcode, operands));

3363 std::vector<HloInstruction*> operands;
3364 for (const ComputationDataHandle& handle : call_request.operands()) {
3365 operands.push_back(lookup_instruction(handle));
3366 }
3367 CHECK_EQ(1, request.embedded_computation_versions_size());
3368 VersionedComputationHandle::Version call_version =
3369 request.embedded_computation_versions(0);
3370 HloComputation* call_computation =
3371 ResolveComputation(call_request.to_apply(), call_version);
3372 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateCall(
3373 request.output_shape(), operands, call_computation));

3381 for (const ComputationDataHandle& operand : cc_request.operands()) {
3382 operands.push_back(lookup_instruction(operand));

3392 std::vector<HloInstruction*> operands;
3393 for (const ComputationDataHandle& operand :
3394 host_compute_request.operands()) {
3395 operands.push_back(lookup_instruction(operand));
3396 }
3397 auto output_shape = host_compute_request.shape();
3398 auto channel_name = host_compute_request.channel_name();
3399 auto cost_estimate_ns = host_compute_request.cost_estimate_ns();
3400 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateHostCompute(
3401 output_shape, operands, channel_name, cost_estimate_ns));
3402 break;
3403 }
3404
3405 case OpRequest::kUnaryOpRequest: {
3406 const UnaryOpRequest& unary_op_request =
3407 request.request().unary_op_request();
3408 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(unary_op_request.operand());
3409 auto hlo_opcode = UnaryOperationToHloOpcode(unary_op_request.unop());
3410 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateUnary(
3411 request.output_shape(), hlo_opcode, operand));

3413 }
3414
3415 case OpRequest::kBinaryOpRequest: {
3416 const BinaryOpRequest& binary_op_request =
3417 request.request().binary_op_request();
3418 HloInstruction* lhs = lookup_instruction(binary_op_request.lhs());
3419 HloInstruction* rhs = lookup_instruction(binary_op_request.rhs());
3420 auto hlo_opcode = BinaryOperationToHloOpcode(binary_op_request.binop());
3421 if (binary_op_request.broadcast_dimensions_size() > 0 &&
3422 ShapeUtil::Rank(lhs->shape()) != ShapeUtil::Rank(rhs->shape())) {
3423 // Emit a broadcast instruction to perform the "broadcast in dimension"
3424 // operation.
3425 HloInstruction* operand_to_broadcast =
3426 ShapeUtil::Rank(lhs->shape()) < ShapeUtil::Rank(rhs->shape()) ? lhs
3427 : rhs;
3428 CHECK_EQ(ShapeUtil::Rank(operand_to_broadcast->shape()),
3429 binary_op_request.broadcast_dimensions().size());
3430
3431 // Construct the bounds of the shape of the kBroadcast instruction
3432 // responsible for the in-dimension broadcast.
3433 std::vector<int64> output_dimensions;
3434 for (int64 size : request.output_shape().dimensions()) {
3435 output_dimensions.push_back(size);
3436 }
3437 for (int64 operand_dim = 0;
3438 operand_dim < ShapeUtil::Rank(operand_to_broadcast->shape());
3439 ++operand_dim) {
3440 int64 output_dim =
3441 binary_op_request.broadcast_dimensions()[operand_dim];
3442 output_dimensions[output_dim] =
3443 operand_to_broadcast->shape().dimensions(operand_dim);
3444 }
3445
3446 Shape broadcast_shape = ShapeUtil::MakeShape(
3447 operand_to_broadcast->shape().element_type(), output_dimensions);
3448
3449 // The broadcast semantics of a client-level binary op broadcast is
3450 // identical to the HLO broadcast semantics so the broadcast_dimensions
3451 // field can just be passed to the instruction builder.
3452 HloInstruction* broadcasted_operand =
3453 add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateBroadcast(
3454 broadcast_shape, operand_to_broadcast,
3455 AsInt64Slice(binary_op_request.broadcast_dimensions())));
3456
3457 lhs = (lhs == operand_to_broadcast) ? broadcasted_operand : lhs;
3458 rhs = (rhs == operand_to_broadcast) ? broadcasted_operand : rhs;
3459 }
3460 if (debug_options_.xla_eliminate_hlo_implicit_broadcast()) {
3461 if (!ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(request.output_shape(), lhs->shape())) {
3462 // lhs side is being implicitly broadcast. Change to explicit.
3463 lhs =
3464 ImplicitBroadcastToExplicitBroadcast(lhs, request.output_shape());
3465 }
3466
3467 if (!ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(request.output_shape(), rhs->shape())) {
3468 rhs =
3469 ImplicitBroadcastToExplicitBroadcast(rhs, request.output_shape());
3470 }
3471 }
3472 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateBinary(
3473 request.output_shape(), hlo_opcode, lhs, rhs));
3474 break;
3475 }
3476
3477 case OpRequest::kReducePrecisionRequest: {
3478 const ReducePrecisionRequest& reduce_precision_request =
3479 request.request().reduce_precision_request();
3480 HloInstruction* operand =
3481 lookup_instruction(reduce_precision_request.operand());
3482 auto exponent_bits = reduce_precision_request.exponent_bits();
3483 auto mantissa_bits = reduce_precision_request.mantissa_bits();
3484 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateReducePrecision(
3485 request.output_shape(), operand, exponent_bits, mantissa_bits));
3486 break;
3487 }
3488
3489 case OpRequest::kTraceRequest: {
3490 const TraceRequest& trace_request = request.request().trace_request();
3491 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(trace_request.operand());
3492 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(
3493 HloInstruction::CreateTrace(trace_request.tag(), operand));
3494 break;
3495 }
3496
3497 case OpRequest::kSendRequest: {
3498 const SendRequest& send_request = request.request().send_request();
3499 HloInstruction* operand = lookup_instruction(send_request.operand());
3500 HloInstruction* send = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateSend(
3501 operand, send_request.channel_handle().handle()));
3502 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateSendDone(send));
3503 break;
3504 }
3505
3506 case OpRequest::kGatherRequest: {
3507 const GatherRequest& gather_request = request.request().gather_request();
3508 HloInstruction* input_operand =
3509 lookup_instruction(gather_request.input());
3510 HloInstruction* gather_indices_operand =
3511 lookup_instruction(gather_request.gather_indices());
3512 std::vector<int64> window_bounds;
3513 c_copy(gather_request.window_bounds(), std::back_inserter(window_bounds));
3514 hlo_instruction = add_instruction(HloInstruction::CreateGather(
3515 request.output_shape(), input_operand, gather_indices_operand,
3516 gather_request.dimension_numbers(), window_bounds));
3517 break;
3518 }
3519
3520 case OpRequest::OP_NOT_SET:
3521 LOG(FATAL) << "OperationRequest doesn't contain a request";
3522
3523 default:
3524 LOG(FATAL) << "Unexpected request type: " << request.request().op_case();
3525 }
3526 (*instructions)[handle.handle()] = hlo_instruction;
3527} // NOLINT(readability/fn_size)

3531StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<HloComputation>> UserComputation::BuildHloComputation(
3532 VersionedComputationHandle::Version version,
3533 HloComputationResolver hlo_resolver, const DebugOptions& debug_options,
3534 bool include_unreachable_instructions) const {
3535 tensorflow::mutex_lock lock(mutex_);
3536
3537 VLOG(2) << "Building HloComputation from UserComputation " << name_
3538 << " at version " << version;
3539 XLA_VLOG_LINES(3, session_computation_.DebugString());
3540
3541 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
3542 std::unique_ptr<HloComputation> hlo_computation,
3543 ComputationLowerer::Lower(
3544 tensorflow::strings::StrCat(name(), ".v", version),
3545 session_computation_, version, std::move(hlo_resolver), debug_options,
3546 include_unreachable_instructions));
3547
3548 return std::move(hlo_computation);
3549}
